---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE, GAME } from '../consts';

const faq = [
  { q: 'Can you turn into a bat in Moonlight Peaks?', a: 'Yes, confirmed at launch. As a vampire you can shapeshift into a bat for fast travel around town at night — accessed via a magic wheel (hold the left shoulder button and pick your form).' },
  { q: 'What is the Hellkitten form?', a: "Confirmed at launch: you can also shapeshift into your three-eyed Hellkitten companion. In Hellkitten form you move faster and can till patches of dirt without a shovel, at a fraction of the normal energy cost." },
  { q: 'What other forms can you shapeshift into?', a: 'Two forms are confirmed at launch — bat and Hellkitten. The developers have teased more forms exist beyond these, but the full list has not been detailed yet.' },
  { q: 'How do you unlock shapeshifting?', a: 'Confirmed at launch: unlocking the Hellkitten form specifically requires finishing four quest strings — "A Bridge Too Far," "Tension in the Crest Garden," "A Croak and a Crest," and "The Dinner Party." Once unlocked, you switch forms from a magic wheel accessed with the left shoulder button.' },
];

const jsonLd = [
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'FAQPage', mainEntity: faq.map((f) => ({ '@type': 'Question', name: f.q, acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: f.a } })) },
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: SITE.url },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Shapeshifting', item: new URL('/shapeshifting', SITE.url).href },
  ] },
];
---
<Base
  title="Moonlight Peaks Shapeshifting — Bat Form & Other Forms"
  description="How shapeshifting works in Moonlight Peaks: turning into a bat to travel at night, the other forms devs have hinted at, and how it fits your vampire powers."
  path="/shapeshifting"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  crumbs={[{ label: 'Shapeshifting' }]}
  showExport
>
  <article class="page">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Entry · Shapeshifting</p>
      <h1>Moonlight Peaks <em>shapeshifting</em></h1>
      <p class="intro">
        One of the perks of being a vampire in {GAME.title} is changing your shape. Two forms are
        confirmed at launch — bat and Hellkitten — accessed via a magic wheel. Updated {SITE.updated}.
      </p>

      <h2>Turn into a bat to get around</h2>
      <p>
        Confirmed at launch: the classic vampire bat form. Shifting into a bat lets you fly around
        the town quickly at night, which is handy when you're juggling the farm, errands and
        socialising before sunrise. <span class="tag-community">Community-reported</span> multiple
        sources describe its specific edge as vertical/elevation traversal — flying over barriers,
        hedges, and gaps that you'd otherwise have to walk around, on top of general speed.
      </p>

      <h2>Hellkitten form — faster movement and free tilling</h2>
      <p>
        Two separate things share the Hellkitten name. From the very start of the game, a three-eyed
        Hellkitten companion pet follows you around and you get to name it (likely "Grim" by default,
        per the official wiki). Separately, <strong>shapeshifting</strong> into a Hellkitten form
        yourself is confirmed to unlock later, once you've finished four quest strings — "A Bridge Too
        Far," "Tension in the Crest Garden," "A Croak and a Crest," and "The Dinner Party." In
        Hellkitten form you move noticeably faster around the map, and pressing Y lets you till dirt
        patches without a shovel at a fraction of the usual energy cost — a genuine quality-of-life
        form, not just cosmetic.
      </p>

      <h2>Other forms are hinted at</h2>
      <p>
        The studio has teased that more forms exist beyond bat and Hellkitten, but the complete set —
        and what each one is good for — hasn't been fully detailed yet. Sources disagree on specifics:
        multiple sources now point to a "Mermaid/Aqua form" for water-based interactions, tied to
        completing "The Mermaid's Wish" quest, though the exact unlock trigger and full details
        aren't independently confirmed by us yet.
      </p>

      <h2>Part of your vampire powers</h2>
      <p>
        Shapeshifting sits alongside the rest of your supernatural abilities and helps you explore
        everything the town has to offer. Both confirmed forms are accessed from a magic wheel (hold
        the left shoulder button, then pick a form). It pairs naturally with <a href="/magic">witchcraft
        and potions</a> — and like everything else in your (un-)life, it works around the rule that
        you return to your coffin before the sun comes up.
      </p>

      <h2>Still being verified</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>The full <strong>list of forms</strong> you can take, beyond the bat.</li>
        <li>How each form <strong>unlocks</strong> and what it's useful for.</li>
        <li>Any limits — energy, timing, or where you can and can't transform.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq">
        {faq.map((f) => (
          <details>
            <summary>{f.q}</summary>
            <p>{f.a}</p>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="callout wip">
        Post-launch entry, updated as the full form list is verified. Related:
        <a href="/magic">magic & potions</a>, <a href="/character-creator">character creator</a>,
        <a href="/beginner-guide">beginner guide</a>, <a href="/achievements">achievements</a>.
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
  <style>
    .tag-community {
      display: inline-block; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.65rem; letter-spacing: 0.02em;
      color: var(--faint); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 999px; padding: 2px 8px;
      margin-right: 6px; vertical-align: middle;
    }
  </style>
</Base>
